==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''universal quantifier''' (''plural'' '''universal quantifiers''')

#{{logic}} The [[operator]], represented by the symbol [[∀]], used in [[predicate calculus]] to indicate that a [[predicate]] is true for all [[member]]s of a specified [[set]].
#: Some verbal equivalents are ''"for each"'' or ''"for every"''.

